WEBVTT

00:04:29.998 --> 00:04:33.228
You expect a financial planner
to remember your risk preferences.

00:04:33.792 --> 00:04:36.617
You want a therapist to recall
how your worldview was shaped

00:04:36.641 --> 00:04:38.041
by your weird family.

00:04:38.649 --> 00:04:40.387
And before a performance review,

00:04:40.411 --> 00:04:44.034
you hope your boss hasn't forgotten
all the good work you've done.

00:04:45.680 --> 00:04:49.643
As a professor, I've always encouraged
my students to develop their memories.

00:04:49.667 --> 00:04:53.397
The problem was, when they'd ask how,
I didn't really have a good answer.

00:04:54.104 --> 00:04:55.971
Then I came across this guy.

00:04:56.429 --> 00:04:59.466
Joshua Foer: I've been to be, well,
a little bit forgetful.

00:04:59.490 --> 00:05:02.172
AG: Joshua Foer is a science journalist.